SIMPLE: religious
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Religious
<hw>Re*li"gious</hw> <pr>(r?-l?j"?s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>religius</ets>, <ets>religious</ets>, F. <ets>religieux</ets>, from
L. <ets>religiosus</ets>. See <er>Religion</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of or pertaining to religion; concerned with religion; teaching, or
setting forth, religion; set apart to religion; <as>as, a
<ex>religious</ex> society; a <ex>religious</ex> sect; a
<ex>religious</ex> place; <ex>religious</ex> subjects, books, teachers,
houses, wars.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our law forbids at their <qex>religious</qex> rites⟦br⟧
My presence.</q> <rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Possessing, or conforming to, religion; pious;
godly; <as>as, a <ex>religious</ex> man, life, behavior,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Men whose lives⟦br⟧
<qex>Religious</qex> titled them the sons of God.</q>
<rj><qau>Mlton</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Scrupulously faithful or exact; strict.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thus, Indianlike,⟦br⟧
<qex>Religious</qex> in my error, I adore⟦br⟧
The sun, that looks upon his worshiper.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Belonging to a religious order; bound by
vows.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>One of them is <qex>religious</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Pious; godly; holy; devout; devotional;
conscientious; strict; rogod; exact.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Religious</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Religious
<hw>Re*li"gious</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A person bound by monastic
vows, or sequestered from secular concern, and devoted to a life of
piety and religion; a monk or friar; a nun.</def>
<rj><au>Addison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Religiously</ent>⟦br⟧
